INSERT INTO `updates` VALUES (1,'Adventure Week 2019','2019-06-03','In-Game Event','Adventure Week 2019 is here! Rock-type Pokemon will appear more frequently in the wild during the event. Hatch Rock-type Pokemon such as Onix, Larvitar, Lileep, Anorith, and Shieldon from 2 km Eggs. Challenge Onix and other Rock-types in raids, and if you\'re lucky, you may encounter a Shiny Onix, Lileep, or Anorith!\r\n<br/>\r\nBonuses:<br/>\r\n- Earn 4X Buddy Candy\r\n- New PokeStop swipes earn 10X XP\r\n- Adventure Sync rewards for walking 50km will earn 50,000 Stardust and 15 Rare Candies',NULL,NULL,'2019-06-11 00:00:00','2019-06-04 00:00:00'),(2,'Slakoth Community Day (June 2019)','2019-06-06','Community Day','Slakoth\'s community day has arrived! Evolve a Vigoroth during the event window and get a Slaking that knows Body Slam. Also you have the chance to find a shiny Slakoth during your travels!',NULL,NULL,'2019-06-09 00:00:00','2019-06-08 00:00:00'),(4,'Website enters BETA!!','2019-06-06','Site News','This info website has finally entered what I consider to be Beta. The interfacing could use a bit polishing, but it works and displays information accordingly. To date, every page has been completed except the Research page. That is a work in progress. For now, game events, raids, and eggs are all reported and accurate. I will continue to flesh out the design of the web app, and hope to expand this into an informative and reliable, yet concise, news source',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(5,'Jirachi Discovered in GameMaster','2019-06-06','Game Update','That\'s right! Jirachi\'s code has been discovered in the Game Master APK. Could this mean the mythical Wishmaker Pokemon finally makes a debut during this year\'s GOFest? Only time will tell!',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(12,'Adventure Sync Glitch - Extended Rewards','2019-06-07','Game Update','Due to Adventure Sync glitched at the beginning of the Adventure Week event, the weekly reward event bonus of 50,000 stardust and 15 rare candies has been extended to next week!',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(22,'Pokestop Submissions Live in Germany and France','2019-06-07','Game Update','The Pokestop submission beta has been expanded to Level 40 players in Germany and France as of today',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(32,'Sponsored Pokestops','2019-06-07','Game Update','Sponsored Pokestops (like Sprint, Starbucks, etc.) can now reward new Research tasks. Thus far, sponsored tasks reward things like 1000+ stardust and rare candies. The information will be collated on the Research page soon',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(52,'Pokemon GO Global Summer Challenge','2019-06-01','In-Game Event','The 2019 Pokemon GO Global Summer Challenge is upon us, trainers! This is a series of in-game events set to tie in with the hotly anticipated Pokemon GO Fests in Chicago (June), Dortmund (July), and Yokohama (August). If all trainer challenges from the GO Fest celebration and the in-game tie in are completed, the shiny variants of each legendary beasts (Raikou, Entei, Suicune) will be released in a Raid Day event!<br/>\n<br/>\nSpark\'s Candy Challenge (June Challenge)<br/>\n- Team Instinct (Global): Complete 15 million research tasks. Reward: Guaranteed 1 Rare Candy per raid<br/>\n- Team Valor (Global): Complete 15 million research tasks. Reward: Guaranteed 1 Rare Candy per raid<br/>\n- Team Mystic (Global): Complete 15 million research tasks. Reward: 2x Hatch Candy<br/>\n<br/>\nIf all bonuses are unlocked, they will run from Tuesday, June 18 to Tuesday, June 25 at 1pm PST, as well as unlocking Shiny Raikou for a Raid Day! Posts will be made for both the Summer Global Challenge June Bonuses and Shiny Raikou Raid Day if they are completed.',NULL,NULL,'2019-06-17 00:00:00','2019-06-13 00:00:00'),(62,'Pokemon Go Fest 2019 (Chicago)','2019-06-10','In-Life','A summer of events is upon us, trainers! Pokemon GO Fest 2019 will be in three locations this year: Chicago (June), Dortmund (July), and Yokohama (August). Trainers both in attendance and around the world will be challenged to various tasks during each GO Fest. If all trainer challenges are completed, the shiny variants of each legendary beast (Raikou, Entei, Suicune) will be released in a Raid Day event!<br/><br/>Spark\'s Candy Challenge (June)<br/>- GO Fest Attendees: Complete 1 million research tasks. Reward: 2x Catch Candy<br/><br/>If all bonuses are unlocked, they will run from Tuesday, June 18 to Tuesday, June 25 at 1pm PST, as well as unlocking Shiny Raikou for a Raid Day! Posts will be made for both the Global Challenge June Bonuses and Shiny Raikou Raid Day, if they are completed.',NULL,NULL,'2019-06-17 00:00:00','2019-06-13 00:00:00'),(72,'Jirachi (and new shinies) Released at GO Fest Chicago!','2019-06-13','Game Update','As expected, Special Research involving Jirachi has been released to GO Fest Chicago attendees. The research involves capturing a number of Pokemon who have certain types, using the Photos feature and encountering Photo Bombs, adding friends, and trading Pokemon from a certain distance.<br/><br/>Additionally, Shiny Abra and Shiny Horsea have made their debuts during the event. Presently, Abra has not been found outside of the event premises, but Shiny Horsea is available globally.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(82,'A Legendary Return - Kyogre Emerges From the Sea','2019-06-14','Raids','The Sea Basin Pokemon is said to have widened the seas and waged battle with Groudon. This Water-type Pokemon is weak against Grass and Electric-type PokÃ©mon. If you\'re lucky, you may encounter a Shiny Kyogre!',NULL,NULL,'2019-06-27 00:00:00','2019-06-18 00:00:00'),(92,'EMEA Slakoth Make-Up','2019-06-25','Community Day','Trainers, we are aware of gameplay issues that impacted the EMEA region during Community Day.<br/><br/>Starting July 4th and 10am until July 7th at 6pm, Slakoth will appear more frequently in your region! Evolve Vigoroth to Slaking during this time and you can access the exclusive move, Body Slam!','https://pokemongohub.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/slakoth.jpg','https://twitter.com/NianticHelp/status/1143583316848734208','2019-07-07 18:00:00','2019-07-04 10:00:00'),(112,'Mudkip Community Day','2019-06-26','Community Day','This July, Community Day features Mudkip and will take place from 4pm to 7pm local time! The pushed-back start time is to allow people to avoid the midsummer heat.<br/><br/> -  FEATURED POKEMON: Mudkip (shiny form release) <br/>- Exclusive Move: TBA<br/>- Bonuses: 3x Catch Stardust, 3 hour Lures','/img/events/mudkip-cday-2019.png','https://pokemongolive.com/events/community-day/','2019-07-21 19:00:00','2019-07-21 16:00:00'),(122,'Raikou Raid Day','2019-06-29','Raids','Congrats on unlocking all Spark\'s Global Challenge bonuses, Trainers! Your hard work helped unlock the ability to battle the Legendary PokÃ©mon Raikou in raids on June 29 at 4 p.m. local time. If you\'re lucky, you may even encounter a Shiny Raikou!','https://pbs.twimg.com/media/D9XvQ5gVUAEekpa.jpg:large','https://twitter.com/PokemonGoApp/status/1141081296505991168','2019-06-29 19:00:00','2019-06-29 16:00:00'),(132,'test','2019-06-29','Raids','test','test','test','2019-06-29 15:23:00','2019-06-29 15:00:00'),(142,'Pokemon GO 3rd Anniversary','2019-06-29','In-Game Event','They say third timeâ€™s the charm. PokÃ©mon journeys begin with a choice between three PokÃ©mon. Your journey in PokÃ©mon GO involved joining one of three teams. Today, we celebrate the third anniversary of PokÃ©mon GOâ€™s release! Throughout this incredible journey, weâ€™ve made countless memories along the way. To commemorate this incredible milestone, you can look forward to these exciting features!<br/><br/>NEW FEATURES:<br/>-Shiny Alolan Forms!: Rattata, Sandshrew, Vulpix, Diglett, Meowth, Geodude, Grimer, and Exeggutor are all now SHINY!<br/>-Team Leader Avatar clothing available in the game shop<br/><br/>From June 28 to July 6, 2019:<br/>-Party Hat Pikachu will appear once daily via the GO Snapshot photobomb! Party Hat Pichu will also be available to hatch from 7 km eggs.<br/><br/>From June 28 to September 2, 2019:<br/>-Jump-Start Research: Trainers can complete new Special Research for helpful rewards that will jump-start their new or continuing adventures. This Special Research is only available this summer for players at level 10 or higher.<br/>-Raid bonuses: Take down Raid Bosses faster and earn extra bonus Premier Balls for raiding with friends!<br/>-Decreased Stardust costs for trading - Trading PokÃ©mon will cost 1/4 less Stardust.<br/><br/>Remember, Trainers: play more with your friends this summer to get the most out of raids and trading!','https://pokemongolive.com/img/posts/anniversaryposter2019.jpg','https://pokemongolive.com/en/post/birthday2019/','2019-09-02 16:00:00','2019-06-28 16:00:00'),(152,'Shadow and Purified Pokemon in Latest APK Teardown!','2019-07-02','Game Update','A new update has rolled out to both iOS and Android users, and within this update is a boat load of new and exciting information! It primarily hints about some huge new features - in this post, we\'ll cover Shadow and Purified Pokemon!<br/><br/><h2>New Features Found in APK</h2><br/><ul><li><strong>Shadow Pokemon:</strong> a new form of PokÃ©mon that have their own stats, move values, candy and Stardust multipliers.</li><br/><li><strong>Purification:</strong> A mechanic that converts Shadow Pokemon into their normal versions, requires stardust and candy to perform.</li><br/><li><strong>Alignments:</strong> Either Shadow or Purified.</li></ul><br/<br/><h2>Everything Known About Shadow Pokemon</h2><br/>Presently, the following Pokemon are listed as having Shadow forms: Bulbasaur, Ivysaur, Venusaur, Charmader, Charmeleon, Charizard, Squirtle, Wartortle, Blastoise, Ratatta, Raticate, Zubat, Golbat, Crobat, Dratini, Dragonair, Dragonite, Snorlax, Mudkip, Marshtomp, Swampert.<br/><br/>Shadow Pokemon have a new attribute called \"Alignment\", which is similar to Gender and Form. Pokemon are either Shadow or Purified, and there is a badge associated with number of purified Pokemon. In order to Purify a Shadow Pokemon, you must spend a certain amount of Stardust and Candy.<br/><br/>Shadow and Purified Forms are handled similar to other Pokemon Forms, like Deoxys. This means they have their own sets of stats and moves. The possibilities for this are endless! We could see a complete shake-up to the Raid and PVP meta with the introduction of Shadow Pokemon who have different base stats and moves (if Shadow Pokemon are even usable outside of their designated feature). We could also see some events down the line that encourage Purifying various Pokemon for some rare rewards (like Sinnoh Stones, Rare Candies, TMs, Raid Passes, and more!), or difficult Raid Battles involving Shadowed Legendaries (curiously, the APK makes no mention of the most famous Shadow Pokemon, Lugia...).<br/></br>One last thing to note - Every Pokemon in the list from the APK is involved from Gen 1 / Kanto EXCEPT for the Mudkip line (and Crobat obviously, but Crobat evolves from Golbat so it makes sense why Crobat is listed). It is quite possible that we get a surprise event or teaser during the Mudkip Community Day this July. Only time will tell though, Trainers!','https://wallpapercave.com/wp/wp2863693.png','https://pokemongohub.net/post/news/new-in-v0-147-1-shadow-pokemon-team-rocket-pokestop-invasions-purification-route-maker-and-3-new-moves/','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(162,'Website enters Beta 1.2','2019-07-02','Site News','This version of the site has a completely revamped Events page, with the same design features soon coming to the new News page. This includes better card sizing, a dynamic background, and buttons that link you to official posts.','','https://fathomless-bastion-62027.herokuapp.com/','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(172,'Shiny Nidoran â™‚ GO Fest Dortmund Tie-In!','2019-07-03','In-Game Event','In celebration of #PokemonGOFest2019, Nidoranâ™‚ will begin appearing more frequently globally on July 4 at 10 a.m. CEST. If youâ€™re lucky, you might even encounter a Shiny Nidoran â™‚!!','https://pbs.twimg.com/media/D-kcWZ0WwAAQbVr?format=jpg&name=medium','https://twitter.com/pokemongoapp/status/1146478754048466944?s=21','2019-07-08 04:00:00','2019-07-04 04:00:00'),(182,'Global Summer Challenge 2019 - GO Fest Dortmund','2019-07-02','In-Game Event','The second round of the Global Summer Challenge 2019 is here! This time, the tie in is involved with GO Fest Dortmund. Candela leads this challenge - letâ€™s see what she has in store!<br/><br/><strong>Candelaâ€™s Global Challenge</strong><ul><li>GO Fest Dortmund: Complete 1 million research tasks. Reward: Unlock 3x Catch XP</li><br/><li>Team Instinct: Complete 15 million research tasks globally. Reward: Unlock 1-hour Lucky Eggs</li><br/><li>Team Valor: Complete 15 million research tasks globally. Reward: Unlock 3x Hatch XP</li><br/><li>Team Mystic: Complete 15 million research tasks globally. Reward: Unlock 2x Raid XP</li><br/></ul>If all of the above bonuses are unlocked, Entei will be available in raids Sunday, July 14, 2019 (time TBA). If youâ€™re lucky, you might encounter Shiny Entei!','https://pokemongolive.com/img/posts/globalchallenge2019info-en.jpg','https://pokemongolive.com/en/post/globalchallenge2019/','2019-07-07 13:00:00','2019-07-04 13:00:00'),(192,'Groudon Erupts Into Battle!','2019-05-23','Raids','Groudon is said to have dueled titanically with Kyogre before falling into a deep slumber. Itâ€™s a Ground-type Pokemon, so, Trainers, this means Water-, Grass-, and Ice-type PokÃ©mon are your best bets for defeating this powerful opponent!','https://pokemongolive.com/img/posts/legendarylineup.jpg','https://pokemongolive.com/en/post/legendarylineup2019/','2019-07-10 16:00:00','2019-06-27 16:00:00'),(202,'Candela\'s XP Challenge Bonuses Unlocked! GO Fest Dortmund 2019 Tie-In','2019-07-07','In-Game Event','Weâ€™ve heard that Candela has been beaming with pride and canâ€™t stop talking about your Global Challenge performance! Enjoy your XP-themed bonus week, Trainers! Youâ€™ve earned it! ','https://pbs.twimg.com/media/D-68lTJWkAAaX6H.jpg:large','https://twitter.com/PokemonGoApp/status/1148062384365420544','2019-07-16 16:00:00','2019-07-09 16:00:00'),(212,'TEAM ROCKET SPOTTED AT GO FEST DORTMUND!','2019-07-06','Game Update','Attention, Trainers! Weâ€™re aware of the reports of a hot air balloon with an â€œRâ€ logo hovering around #PokemonGOFest2019 over the past few days in Dortmund, Germany. Weâ€™re monitoring the situation and looking into it. ','https://pbs.twimg.com/media/D-z4KWlX4AAYwcJ.jpg:large','https://twitter.com/PokemonGoApp/status/1147554047475507207','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(222,'Global Challenge Reward: Entei Raid Day','2019-07-10','Raids','On July 14, from 4:00pm - 7:00pm local time in every time zone, 5 free Raid Passes will be obtainable and Entei will be available in raids with an expected shiny variant!','https://pbs.twimg.com/media/D_URm5VXYAEzvq7.jpg','https://twitter.com/PokemonGoApp/status/1149844642743107585','2019-07-14 19:00:00','2019-07-14 16:00:00'),(232,'Armored Mewtwo Takes Over Raids','2019-07-05','Raids','Mewtwo returns...with a new look. For a limited time, you can encounter this Psychic-type PokÃ©mon in five-star raids.\r\n<br/>\r\n<h3>Date + Time</h3>\r\n<br/>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Armored Mewtwo will appear in five-star raids from July 10 at 1:00 p.m. PDT to July 31 at 1 p.m. PDT</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br/>\r\n<h3>Features</h3>\r\n<br/>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>For the first time in Pokemon GO, Armored Mewtwo will be available to challenge in raids for a limited time!</li>\r\n<li>Do you consider yourself a Mewtwo Trainer? Show off your prowess for power and aesthetics with some stylish new items coming to the Style Shop!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br/>\r\nDonâ€™t miss this chance to encounter Armored Mewtwo. Are you up for the challenge?','https://pbs.twimg.com/media/D-rGj7NXUAAWM5C.jpg:large','https://pokemongolive.com/post/armoredmewtworaids2019','2019-07-31 16:00:00','2019-07-10 16:00:00'),(242,'Rayquaza Descends from the Sky!','2019-07-30','Raids','Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years in the ozone layer, descending only to put the clash between Kyogre and Groudon to rest. Seeing as the Sea Basin PokÃ©mon and the Continent PokÃ©mon have both been active recently, itâ€™s no surprise that this normally reclusive PokÃ©mon has reappeared in their place.\r\n<br/>\r\n<strong>Features:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Rayquaza raids from July 31 to September 2</li>\r\n<li>If you\'re lucky, you may get a SHINY RAYQUAZA!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br/>\r\nGood luck, Trainers! Go get that Rayquaza!','https://pokemongolive.com/img/posts/shinyrayquazaraid.jpg','https://pokemongolive.com/en/post/shinyrayquazaraid/','2019-09-02 16:00:00','2019-07-31 16:00:00'),(252,'Team GO Rocket Disruption','2019-07-25','In-Game Event','Team GO Rocketâ€™s arrival seems to have disrupted Pokemon habitats! We have yet to understand why these PokÃ©mon in particular are suddenly appearing more frequently. Perhaps they have some special significance wherever Team GO Rocket came from?\r\n<br/>\r\n<strong>Features</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shiny Ekans, Koffing, Sneasel, and Zubat are now available in the wild and in raids!</li>\r\n<li>The following Pokemon will hatch more frequently from Eggs: Rattata, Ekans, Sandshrew, Zubat, Meowth, Machop, Magnemite, Grimer, Gastly, Drowzee, Cubone, Koffing, Murkrow, Sneasel, Houndour, and Poochyena.</li>\r\n<li>Raids will feature Pokemon that are significant to Team GO Rocket.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br/>\r\nWe hope these are the last of the disruptions weâ€™ll see from Team GO Rocket... In the meantime, Trainers, keep exploring the world around you, and let us know what you discover.','https://pokemongolive.com/img/posts/teamgorocketdisruption2019.jpg','https://pokemongolive.com/en/post/teamgorocketdisruption2019/','2019-08-01 16:00:00','2019-07-25 16:00:00');
